edu.usm.cos420.example1.service

Interface ExampleService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Example1Service

    public interface ExampleService
    The Example1 Service Interface is based a design pattern which aims to organize the functionality of the application into logical units that are typically layered on top of much of the low level functionality of the application. This organization helps support service oriented architectures.
